  "_comment_scenario": "Limited Liability Partnership — UK LLP with Corporate General Partner, Multiple Limited Partners and Natural Person Directors. This example demonstrates AMLR Art. 26 and FATF R.24 beneficial ownership disclosure for Meridian Capital LLP (UK), a private digital asset fund structured as a limited liability partnership. The LLP is itself the originating VASP. Under the LLP agreement (LPA), management and control are exclusively vested in the General Partner (GP); limited partners have no management rights. Partnership interest breakdown: [GP, 0% economic / 100% management control] Meridian Capital GP Ltd (UK); [LP, 45%] Priya Sharma Investments Ltd (Mauritius); [LP, 35%] Ashworth Pension Fund Ltd (UK); [LP, 10%] Dr. Arjun Sharma (UK); [LP, 10%] Sita Patel (UK). UBO determination: Priya Sharma (UK/India) is the sole UBO because (i) she is the sole director and 100% shareholder of Meridian Capital GP Ltd — the General Partner holding all management and voting rights under the LPA; (ii) she also beneficially owns 100% of Priya Sharma Investments Ltd (the largest LP). Despite GP partners in an LLP having no formal ownership stake, control through the GP role constitutes DE_FACTO_CONTROL and CONTRACTUAL control for UBO purposes under AMLR Art. 26(1). FATF Guidance on Transparency of LPs (June 2023) explicitly requires identification of GP controllers as UBOs.",
